…Plots Of Land For Each Player, Official If They Win Title LAGOS – Monetary incentives have continued to come the way of Super Eagles as Bamidele Onalaja, the Group Managing Director of Revolution Plus, a renowned property development company, has promised the Nigerian national team N1 million per goal from the knockout stage of the ongoing Africa Cup of Nations in Cameroon. Onalaja, in a video call with Ahmed Musa, the team’s captain, also said each member of the team (players and officials) will get a plot of land each in any location of their choice (Lagos, Abuja, Abeokuta, Port Harcourt, Ibadan) if they eventually win the title. AFCON 2021: Tough Test For Super Eagles As Nigeria Face Familiar… AFCON 2021: Football Fans Urge Super Eagles To Ensure Victory He has equally redeemed the N1million per goal pledge he made during the 2022 World Cup qualification 2nd round matches against Liberia and Cape Verde where the Super Eagles scored 4 goals in both matches. Captain, Ahmed Musa has confirmed the receipt of N4 million. “I just want to make you guys happy. The one I promised during the World Cup qualifier I have redeemed. Also, let me say, for all goals you guys score at this knockout stage of the AFCON, Revolution Plus properties will pay you guys a million per goal. “Also if you guys lift the AFCON, every player and coach will have a plot of Land each either in Lagos, Abuja, Port Harcourt, Ibadan, Abeokuta or anywhere of your choice.“We are Revolution Properties are so excited about you and we are praying for you,” Onalaja enthused.